CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, September 9, 1967, pg. 15, reads: "ULG Boat Ride - For the past few years, one of the social highlights of the season has been a boat ride sponsored by the Urban League Guild of Pittsburgh. This year was no exception and a happy throng was on hand for the event held recently...No one had more fun than this group which includes Marguerite Walker, Gertrude Dews, Arthur Edmonds, executive director of Urban League; Mildred Lawler, Eunice Brevard, Ronald R. Davenport, president of Urban League Board, and Elethia Wells. - All Harris photos."
TitMainTitle: Group, seated from left: Marguerite Walker, Elethia Wells; standing: Gertrude Dews, Arthur Edmonds, Mildred Lawler, Eunice Brevard, and Ronald R. Davenport, posed on riverboat deck for Urban League Guild of Pittsburgh's annual boat ride, Downtown
